<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>28-5402(Perm)</num>
  <heading>Prohibited practices.</heading>
  <para>
    <num undesignated="true">(a)</num>
    <text>A retailer shall not discriminate against cash as a form of payment for goods or services, including by:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>Refusing to accept cash as a form of payment;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>Posting signs on the premises that cash payment is not accepted; or</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(3)</num>
      <text>Charging a higher price to consumers who pay cash.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 23-187" type="History">Mar. 16, 2021, D.C. Law 23-187, ยง 2(c), 68 DCR 1031</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
